&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO MATERNITY COVER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available at Denbigh Community Hospital to cover maternity leave. We are looking for an enthusiastic Band 6 Emergency Nurse Practitioner to work as a pivotal member of the Team in Minor Injuries/Outpatients/IV suite&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The busy Minor Injury Department is ENP led where a variety of injuries can be seen and treated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an Out Patients Department which has many visiting Consultants and Nurse Specialists from different specialities. We also have a busy IV Suite which provides Blood Transfusions and IV therapy for many patients around the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 10th Novmber, 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suzannah Jayne Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Day Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Suzannah.Jones@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
